do list” ([thirdeyedata.ai](https://thirdeyedata.ai/technologies/azure-ai-foundry-agent-service)).\n\nManaged Cloud Service with SDK Support  \n- Foundry Agent Service is available as a fully managed cloud offering, complete with SDKs for languages including Python, C#, and TypeScript. This simplifies agent development with seamless tool-calling and deployment workflows ([microsoft.github.io](https://microsoft.github.io/aitour26-WRK540-unlock-your-agents-potential-with-model-context-protocol/agent-service-overview/)).  \n- It supports rapid deployment, scalable infrastructure, custom integrations, built-in tools, conversation state management, and broad compatibility with AI model variants ([microsoft.github.io](https://microsoft.github.io/build-your-first-agent-with-azure-ai-agent-service-workshop/)).\n\nTool Integration & Extensibility  \n- Agents can invoke both built-in tools (e.g., web search, code interpreter, file search, function calling) and custom tools like MCP (Model Context Protocol), OpenAPI-based connectors, or even agent-to-agent communications ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/foundry/agents/concepts/tool-catalog)).  \n- The Foundry tool catalog simplifies discovering and configuring these tools, enabling agents to take meaningful actions beyond text generation ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/foundry/agents/concepts/tool-catalog)).\n\nHosted Agents & Deployment Lifecycle  \n- For more complex or custom agent code, Foundry supports hosting containerized agents using managed hosting. These “hosted agents” can be built with frameworks like LangGraph or Microsoft Agent Framework and deployed as Docker containers, with the service handling scaling, observability, and lifecycle (create, start, stop, update) ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/foundry/agents/concepts/hosted-agents)).  \n- The Azure Developer CLI provides tools to streamline deployment: the `azd up` command provisions resources, builds container images, and publishes agents—typically within 5–10 minutes—with managed identity and security preconfigured ([visualstudiomagazine.com](https://visualstudiomagazine.com/articles/2025/11/19/azure-developer-cli-adds-ai-agent-extension-for-foundry-deployments.aspx)).\n\nPublishing & Distribution  \n- Once an agent is ready, it can be **published** to create an Agent Application—a durable, production-grade Azure resource with its own endpoint, authentication policy, Entra identity, and RBAC governance ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/foundry/agents/how-to/publish-agent)).  \n- Published agents can then be distributed through Microsoft channels such as Microsoft\u202F365 Copilot, Microsoft\u202FTeams, or the Entra Agent Registry ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/foundry/agents/overview)).\n\nSecurity, Governance & Enterprise Readiness  \n- Designed with enterprise governance in mind, Foundry Agent Service supports identity controls, network isolation, data residency, and bring-your-own Azure resources (e.g., Cosmos\u202FDB, Azure AI Search) for compliance ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/foundry/agents/overview)).  \n- Guardrails are built-in to mitigate unsafe outputs and prompt injection attacks, with Responsible AI guidance and integration available ([learn.microsoft.com](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/foundry/agents/overview)).\n\nManagement, Observability & Control Plane  \n- The service includes capabilities for observing and managing agent behavior: Foundry Control Plane offers end‑to‑end observability, enhancing developer productivity and enterprise trust ([windowsmode.com](https://www.windowsmode.com/microsoft-and-nvidia-gtc-scaling-ai-with-foundry-azure-ai-physical-ai/)).  \n- It supports multi-agent orchestration and event-driven workflows, enabling robust enterprise automation scenarios across industries like customer support and data analysis ([latenode.com](https://latenode.com/blog/ai-agents-autonomous-systems/enterprise-ai-agent-solutions/microsoft-azure-ai-foundry-agent-service-2025-complete-review-implementation-guide)).\n\nSummary of Key Features  \n- Fully managed cloud-native platform for AI agents with SDKs in Python, C#, TypeScript  \n- Rich tool ecosystem: built-in tools, MCP, OpenAPI, A2A (agent-to-agent)  \n- Support for hosted containerized agents with auto-scaling and observability  \n- Streamlined deployment via Azure Developer CLI and Azure tooling  \n- Publishing capabilities for durable endpoint exposure and secure distribution  \n- Enterprise-grade security, governance, and compliance features  \n- Observability through Foundry Control Plane and support for complex, multi-agent workflows\n\nFoundry Agent Service is Microsoft's flagship platform for building intelligent agentic systems in enterprise contexts. It brings together powerful AI models, tools, governance, and deployment infrastructure to enable production-grade agent experiences that are secure, scalable, and integrable with existing enterprise systems.","annotations":[{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://thirdeyedata.ai/technologies/azure-ai-foundry-agent-service","start_index":646,"end_index":734,"title":"Azure AI Foundry Agent Service: Tool for Deploying AI Agents"},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://thirdeyedata.ai/technologies/azure-ai-foundry-agent-service","start_index":956,"end_index":1044,"title":"Azure AI Foundry Agent Service: Tool for Deploying AI Agents"},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://microsoft.github.io/aitour26-WRK540-unlock-your-agents-potential-with-model-context-protocol/agent-service-overview/","start_index":1317,"end_index":1466,"title":"AI Foundry Agent Services - Unlock your Agents Potential with MCP"},{"type":"url_citation","url":"https://microsoft.github.io/build-your-first-agent-with-azure-ai-agent-service-workshop/","start_index":1642,"end_index":1755,"title":"Buil